 request header if it contains a certain string.\r\n\r\nThis works with \"mitmproxy-4.0.4-linux\":\r\n\r\n```\r\n./mitmproxy --replacements \":~hq User-Agent:Mozilla(.+):CUSTOMAGENT\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith \"mitmproxy-5.2-linux\", this at least replaces the `User-Agent`, but is missing my \"certain string condition\":\r\n\r\n```\r\n./mitmproxy --modify-headers \"|~hq .+|User-Agent|CUSTOMAGENT\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nHow do I add my `Mozilla` condition in v5?\r\n\r\nNone of these work:\r\n\r\n```\r\n./mitmproxy --modify-headers \"|~hq ^(.*?)Mozilla(.*?)$|User-Agent|CUSTOMAGENT\"\r\n\r\n./mitmproxy --modify-headers \"/~hq .*?Mozilla.*?/User-Agent/CUSTOMAGENT\"\r\n\r\n./mitmproxy --modify-headers \"|~hq Mozilla|User-Agent|CUSTOMAGENT\"\r\n\r\n./mitmproxy --modify-headers \"|~hq User-Agent: Mozilla|User-Agent|CUSTOMAGENT\"\r\n\r\n./mitmproxy --modify-headers \"|~hq \\\"^(.*?)Mozilla(.*?)$\\\"|User-Agent|CUSTOMAGENT\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nI've been trying for hours, and I feel like I've tried every variation under the sun. There's a very small chance it's a bug, but most likely I'm just doing it wrong. If it matters, this system is Ubuntu 16.04.\r\n\r\n\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"uvtzxpm","id":24996578,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0OTk2NTc4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/24996578?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/uvtzxpm","html_url":"https://github.com/uvtzxpm","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uvtzxpm/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uvtzxpm/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uvtzxpm/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uvtzxpm/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uvtzxpm/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uvtzxpm/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uvtzxpm/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uvtzxpm/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/use